name: La Calavera Catrina
description:
Do not stand at my grave and weep. I
am not there, I do not sleep. I am a
thousand winds that blow. I am the
diamond glints on the snow. I am the
sunlight on the ripened grain. I am the
gentle Autumn's rain. When you
awaken in the morning hush, I am the
swift uplifting rush of quiet birds in
circled flight. I am the soft stars that
shine at night. Do not stand at my
grave and cry: I am not there, I did not
die. - Immortality by Clare Harner
Lyon, 1909-1977
